What information do we collect from you?
What personal data we collect from you will depend on what services on our Sites you use. If you access our web site without logging in or engaging in electronic commerce, we will collect:
Internet Protocol (“IP”) address: An IP address is a number automatically assigned to the computer that you are using by your Internet service provider and is identified and logged automatically in our server log files whenever you use certain of our other Sites, along with the time of the visit, the page(s) or products that were visited and other information related to your visit. We use IP addresses for purposes such as calculating usage levels, diagnosing server problems, administering our Sites, and improving user experiences. We may be able to ascertain your general location through your IP address. Your IP address and date/timestamp of the visit of our Site will be stored in a cookie as explained in the section “Do you use cookies?” below. We process this data to ensure a positive user experience for you.
Mobile device identifiers. We collect your unique device ID, advertising identifier (IDFA, AdID, etc.) and/or other similar data regarding the mobile device you use to access our Sites. We may also collect geo-location information from your mobile device. We collect your unique device ID when you use the FontExplorer X Pro desktop client. If you link your fontexplorerx.com account to the FontExplorer X Pro desktop client, or sign into your fontexplorerx.com account using the desktop client, the FontExplorer X Pro desktop client also collects your long in credentials. Additionally, the FontExplorer X Pro desktop client uses Google Analytics. For more information, please refer to the section entitled “What other technologies do we use?” below.
When you register for an account on one of our Sites (as a customer, an invited user or as a font designer or foundry), subscribe to receive our communications, update your account information, enter our contests or sweepstakes, respond to surveys, make purchases, contact us with questions or comments, apply for a job, connect with us through social networking platforms, submit user generated content or participate in our online forums or promotions, interact with our salespeople, and/or contact our customer service departments we may additionally collect the following information:
Your full name, username, password, email address, telephone number, physical or billing mail addresses, if you pay for a purchase by credit card the last 4 digits of your credit card number (the entire number is sent to a third party payment processor, see below) and credit card expiration date, if you receive royalties from us your social security number or tax identification number as applicable, geo-location and other information you provide to us when accessing or using one of our Sites, and if you have contacted us or accessed one of our Sites on behalf of a business or other entity, your professional contact information and any relevant details about your business or entity as it relates to you;
Comments you may make on one of our forums, attitudes and opinions about and usage of our products that are attributable to you, your demographics, your location, your interests, your professional or lifestyle information, your job description, your level of satisfaction with our Sites, your purchasing behavior or history, and your browsing, downloading and other internet- or mobile-based activities;
Information about you contained in a resume or curriculum vitae, details about yourself that you submit in connection with a job application or inquiry including profile information on any social networking site (for example LinkedIn) if you apply for a job in that manner;
Information about you that is publicly available or provided by third parties such as information that is posted on social media sites, blogs and other websites; and/or
Information about you contained in E-mail lists, mailing lists, customer leads, and/or other data we may purchase or obtain from third parties for our advertising and marketing purposes.
When you use the MyFonts mobile application, we do not collect personal information directly from you, but the MyFonts mobile application uses analytics providers that collect personal information. For more information about these analytics providers, please refer to the section entitled “What other technologies do we use?” below.
When you use our web font services for your web pages or digital advertisements, in each case where our web font tracking code has been deployed, the IP address of each visitor to your website or digital advertisement is transferred to our third party service provider. The transfer of such IP address takes place in order to count the page views for our licensees and to prevent illicit use of our web font software (Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR), but the IP addresses are not transmitted to us, stored, or otherwise processed by our third party service provider.
We may link information you’ve provided us with to other information about you, such as linking your name with your geographic location or your browsing or purchasing history, and we also may link personal information with information we receive about you from third parties. If we link your personal information with any other information collected or received from you or third parties, we will treat that linked information as personal information. We may ask you to input a credit card number when making a purchase, however all credit card numbers you input through one of our Sites are processed and/or stored by a third party credit card or payment facilitator or processor, and not by us.
How do we use the information we collect from you?
We may use the information we collect about you for a variety of purposes, such as to:
complete transactions you have requested or fulfill orders you have placed, including orders you may have placed through us with third party font foundries;
respond to or follow-up on your comments, reviews, inquiries including product inquiries and other requests;
deliver targeted advertising, videos, communications, product solutions, and content;
ensure compliance with the terms of any agreement you have entered into with us;
prevent fraud as it relates to certain of our products and services;
conduct research and analysis related to our business or Sites;
provide third party brands with information about your interaction with our Sites as they relate to such third party brands;
improve our Sites and tailor them to your usage or preferences;
communicate with you about contests, sweepstakes, coupons, product and pricing promotions or other matters which you have entered or joined or for which you have requested information;
implement social networking features you have activated;
publish your reviews, comments, photos, videos and other content you have posted to one of our interactive or user-generated features;
communicate with you about your account or your use of our Sites, including the delivery of customer service;
enforce the Terms of Use of our Sites or otherwise manage our business;
send you promotional messages in email or text form that we think will be of interest to you and/or to invite you to events, both in instances where you have opted-in or not opted-out of receiving such messages; and/or
send you important messages about your use of our Sites, products or services.
How and with whom do we share and disclose information we collect from you?
We do not sell or rent your personal information to third parties. We share your personal information with our subsidiaries and affiliates. Also, we deliver and obtain certain content of our Sites through and/or using third party applications, our or third party programming interfaces, extensions that are hosted on our Sites or through other third party websites, social and professional networking platforms, and/or messaging platforms. When you use our Sites or otherwise participate in services, products, applications, or connect with or “accept” or “allow” third party applications, networks, platforms or services through our Sites, you are authorizing those third parties to receive your information and additionally to potentially share any or all of your information with us, based on your privacy or other settings on that particular third party’s network or platform. The purposes of such information exchange are:
to conduct research and/or analysis regarding our Sites, market trends, our products and services as well as other topics;
to allow third party font foundries – from which you may have licensed a font through us – to provide you customer service, react to your inquiries or solve product issues;
to allow service providers to provide their services in connection with some of our Sites;
to prevent parties from sending promotional messages on our behalf to people who have asked us to not send such messages; and/or
if you have opted-in to receive promotional communications from us, to send tailored promotional communications to you jointly offering a product or service.
We rely on third party service providers to perform a variety of services on our behalf, and we may disclose your personal information to such service providers, for example fulfillment services, business intelligence providers, ad serving companies, customer service providers, delivery services, e-commerce providers, credit card or payment processers and research and analytics providers. We do not authorize these third parties’ to use your personal information for purposes other than for which it has been provided, and we do not authorize these third parties to disclose such information to unauthorized parties.
If we share your personal information with any third party, we will require such third party to maintain the confidentiality of your personal information, comply with applicable laws related to the sharing of personal information and we will not authorize those third parties to use personal information that we provide for their direct marketing purposes unless we have explicitly given you the option to opt-in or opt-out of that disclosure. If you are a resident of the State of California, you may ask us at any time to refrain from sharing your personal information with third parties for their marketing purposes.
Please tell us your preference by contacting us at [email protected] or by writing to us at:
Monotype Imaging Holdings Inc.
